    <!-- Help Manual -->
    <string name="help_title">Help &amp; Usage</string>
    <string name="help_message">Hi there, a few quick pointers…\n\n<b>Import invoices:</b>\nTap + and pick XML or PDF files (long-press for multi-select). You can also share files straight from your mail app into ZUGFeRD &amp; E-Invoice Reader.\n\n<b>ZUGFeRD &amp; Factur-X PDFs:</b>\nHybrid PDFs are detected automatically — the embedded XML is extracted, and the original PDF is kept as an attachment.\n\n<b>Supported formats:</b>\nUBL / Peppol BIS 3.0, XRechnung (UBL and CII), ZUGFeRD 1.x and 2.x, Factur-X, and Polish <b>KSeF FA(3)</b> for invoices issued in Poland.\n\n<b>Invoices vs. credit notes:</b>\nTold apart automatically — credit notes (incl. KSeF KOR / KOR_ZAL / KOR_ROZ) are flagged with a red chip and shown with a negative amount. KSeF correction invoices also display the original number and reason.\n\n<b>Detail view:</b>\nThree tabs: rendered invoice, raw XML (with live search), and the original PDF if attached. Use <b>Open / Paid</b> to mark an invoice as settled.\n\n<b>Filter the list:</b>\nUse the chips above the list for <i>All / Unpaid / Overdue</i>, and the date range picker to limit to a period.\n\n<b>Due-date reminders:</b>\nUnder <i>Reminders…</i> you can switch on daily notifications and choose how many days ahead.\n\n<b>Export:</b>\nUnder <i>Export…</i> create a CSV (UTF-8) for your tax advisor — optionally as a ZIP bundle including the original XML/PDF files.\n\n<b>Dashboard:</b>\nThe Dashboard menu shows expenses per month and your top suppliers.\n\n<b>AI assistant:</b>\nUnder <i>AI Settings</i> add an LLM provider (OpenAI, Gemini, Claude, Mistral, OpenRouter, Langdock or a generic OpenAI-compatible endpoint) — paste your API key, load the models and pick a default. Then open an invoice and tap the speech bubble to ask questions about it. Note: the invoice data is sent to the provider you chose.\n\n<b>Create invoices (Creator):</b>\nUse the <b>Create</b> tab in the bottom bar to switch to Creator mode and issue your own ZUGFeRD invoices (EN 16931).\n\n<b>Notes &amp; categories:</b>\nOpen an invoice and tap the line above the tabs to add a bookkeeping note and category — both go into the CSV export.\n\n<b>Backup:</b>\nUnder the menu you can create a full backup (database + attachments) or restore one — your safety net against device loss.\n\n<b>Delete:</b>\nLong-press a row in the list.\n\n<i>Tip: every screen and panel has its own ? help button.</i></string>

