    <!-- Context-specific help per screen / sheet -->
    <string name="help_detail"><b>Detail view</b>\n\nThree tabs: the rendered invoice, the raw XML (with live search) and the original PDF if one is attached.\n\n<b>Open / Paid:</b> toggle whether the invoice is settled.\n\n<b>Note &amp; category:</b> tap the line above the tabs to add a bookkeeping note and a category — both appear in the CSV export and are searchable.\n\n<b>Ask AI:</b> the speech bubble opens a chat about this invoice (needs an AI provider in AI Settings).</string>
    <string name="help_dashboard"><b>Dashboard</b>\n\nOverview of your invoices for the selected period (use the filter at the top).\n\n<b>KPIs:</b> total, count, open and overdue amounts.\n<b>Charts:</b> payment status, expenses per month, a paid-vs-total trend and your top suppliers.\n<b>VAT per quarter:</b> net/VAT/gross per quarter for your VAT return.\n\nCredit notes count negatively everywhere.</string>
    <string name="help_ai"><b>AI settings</b>\n\nAdd one or more AI providers (OpenAI, Gemini, Claude, Mistral, OpenRouter, Langdock or a generic OpenAI-compatible endpoint).\n\nAdd a provider, paste your API key, load the models and pick one — then mark an entry as the default.\n\nAfterwards open any invoice and tap the speech bubble to ask about it.\n\n<b>Privacy:</b> the invoice content is sent to the provider you choose.</string>
    <string name="help_creator_list"><b>ZUGFeRD &amp; E-Invoice Creator</b>\n\nCreate your own e-invoices as hybrid ZUGFeRD PDF/A-3 (EN 16931).\n\n<b>New invoice:</b> starts a draft.\n<b>Company profile:</b> your sender data — fill it in first.\n<b>Customers:</b> your customer master for quick reuse.\n\nDrafts can be edited; <i>generated</i> invoices are final — tap one to view, share or duplicate it as a new draft (handy for recurring invoices).</string>
    <string name="help_creator_edit"><b>Invoice editor</b>\n\nEnter the number, dates, your customer and the line items (description, quantity, unit, unit price, VAT rate). Totals update live.\n\n<b>From customer master:</b> fills the buyer fields from a saved customer.\n\n<b>Create:</b> runs an EN 16931 check first — errors block, warnings can be skipped — then produces the hybrid ZUGFeRD PDF. A generated invoice can no longer be edited.</string>
    <string name="help_company_profile"><b>Company profile</b>\n\nYour sender data, used on every invoice you create. EN 16931 needs at least a full address plus a VAT ID or tax number.\n\n<b>Logo:</b> optional, shown on the PDF.\n<b>Numbering:</b> auto-suggests the next number (still editable).\n<b>Payment term:</b> pre-fills the due date (issue date + N days).\n<b>Storage:</b> where generated PDFs are saved.</string>
    <string name="help_creator_customers"><b>Customer master</b>\n\nSaved customers for your created invoices. New customers are added automatically when you generate an invoice; you can also add, edit or delete them here.\n\nIn the editor, <i>From customer master</i> fills the buyer fields with one tap.</string>
    <string name="help_creator_articles"><b>Articles &amp; services</b>\n\nYour catalog of recurring articles and services with unit, unit price and VAT rate. In the invoice editor, <i>From catalog</i> adds a pre-filled line item — quantity and all other fields stay editable.</string>
    <string name="help_creator_dashboard"><b>Revenue dashboard</b>\n\nKey figures for your created invoices: revenue, open and overdue amounts, payment status, revenue per month, VAT per quarter and top customers.\n\nOnly <i>generated</i> invoices count — drafts are excluded, credit notes count negatively. Mark invoices as paid via the invoice list.</string>
    <string name="help_export"><b>Export</b>\n\nCreate a CSV (UTF-8, semicolon-separated) of your invoices for the chosen period — ready for your tax advisor or spreadsheet.\n\n<b>Bundle as ZIP:</b> additionally includes the original XML and PDF files per invoice.\n\nThe CSV includes category and note columns. Credit notes are exported with a negative amount.</string>
    <string name="help_reminders"><b>Due-date reminders</b>\n\nSwitch on a daily check that notifies you about invoices coming due.\n\n<b>Lead time:</b> how many days ahead to be reminded (0/3/7/14).\n\n<b>Check now</b> runs the check immediately. On Android 13+ the app asks for notification permission when you enable this.</string>
    <string name="help_ai_credential"><b>AI provider</b>\n\n<b>Provider:</b> pick your service (or <i>Generic</i> for any OpenAI-compatible endpoint).\n<b>API key:</b> paste your key, load the models, then pick one.\n<b>Label:</b> a name to recognise this entry.\n\nThe key is stored only on this device. When you chat about an invoice, its content is sent to this provider.</string>
</resources>
